               <head>Commentary on Qasidah-yi Ta'iyyah</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of a work by Turkah Khujandī Iṣfahānī, Abū Muḥammad Ṣāʾin al-Dīn ʿAlī ibn Afz̤al al-Dīn‏</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2010115018 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85006336" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Or_16862-item1">
                     <note>
                        <p>A metaphysical commentary on <title>al-Qaṣīdah al-Tāʾīyah</title>, the famous mystical ode by <persName key="viaf_118486738" role="ant">Ibn al-Fāriz̤</persName>. By <persName key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164658446.0x000001 viaf_45460576" role="aut">Ṣāʾin al-Dīn ʿAlī Turkah Iṣfahānī</persName> (d. ca. 830/1427).
                        </p>
                        <p>Begins:
Basmala  Ḥamd-i bī-ḥadd Khudāyī-rā ki nihāl-i būd va nā-būd az riyāẓ-i arāẓī-i Kān Allāh maqṭū‘ karda dar ‘ayn-i ān qaṭ‘ ḥażratī-rā… 
</p>
                        <p>Iran. Dated 14 Zū l-Ḥijja 806/22 June 1404. </p>
                        <p>Good naskhī, selectively vocalised, with archaic features including postvocalic dhāl (sporadically) and two dots under final yā (consistently). 21 lines. Marginal corrections. Headings and Arabic verses in red. Small, elegant illuminated headpiece, 2v. 182 folios. 18 x 11 cm. Some damp staining. Later plain brown leather binding, upside-down, with flap and marbled endpapers. </p>
                        <p>Purchased from Bonhams (23 April 2012, Lot 27). </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian &amp; Arabic</textLang>
